This paper deals with a distributed streaming model and focuses on a basic counting problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Databases (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the tradeoff between accuracy and processing speed, which falls under the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which could also place it in the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
